## Rules / Regole (MUST FOLLOW)

> **IT**: Regole che l'agente DEVE seguire SEMPRE. Sii specifico — non generico!  
> **EN**: Rules the agent MUST ALWAYS follow. Be specific — not generic!

### Code Rules
- [es: Ogni endpoint deve avere un test corrispondente]
- [es: NO direct DB queries in routes — sempre tramite service]
- [es: ALL functions devono avere docstrings con esempi]
- [es: Type hints su TUTTI i parametri e return types]
- [es: Nessun file hardcodato — sempre config/env vars]

### Git Rules
- [es: Conventional commits: feat/fix/docs/refactor/test: description [TASK-XXX]]
- [es: NEVER committare .env, secrets, o credentials]
- [es: Use `git add <file>` — NEVER `git add -A`]
- [es: Squash merges su feature branches]
- [es: Tags for versions: v1.0.0, v1.0.1, etc]

### Testing Rules
- [es: Minimum 80% code coverage]
- [es: Test ALL edge cases, not just happy paths]
- [es: Tests must be independent (no shared state)]

### Database Rules
- [es: Always use migrations (Alembic/Prisma)]
- [es: NO direct SQL — sempre via ORM]
- [es: Add indexes for query filters]

**Example / Esempio**:
```
✓ Every endpoint MUST have a test
✓ NO direct DB queries in routes (use services)
✓ ALL functions MUST have docstrings
✓ Commit format: feat/fix/docs: description [TASK-XXX]
✓ NEVER use git add -A (use selective commits)
✓ NEVER commit .env or secrets
✓ Type hints required on all public functions
```

